The paper proposes a method for selecting logical hidden Markov models from data using generalized expectation maximization and inductive logic programming refinement operators. This involves optimizing parameters and exploring different abstraction levels, which are common themes in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with sequences of logical atoms, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of hidden Markov models is a common technique in data science (cs.DS).
